## Principles

- Fix ONLY what is broken. Do not refactor surrounding code.
- If the error is an import path or module name, verify the actual file exists at that path before guessing.
- If the root cause is in a different file (e.g., wrong export, missing function), fix what you can in THIS file and note that the other file also needs changes — a separate agent handles that.
- Do not suppress errors with bare except or empty catch blocks.
- Do not change function signatures unless the diagnosis specifically requires it.
- A fix that changes the least code is the best fix.

